# Introduction to Python

Python ek bohot hi powerful aur popular programming language hai. Ye easy to understand, high-level aur interpreted programming language hai.

**Q. Python simple kyun hai?**
Kyunki agar humko kuch print karna ho, toh hum sirf `print()` likhte hain aur jo string print karani hai wo brackets mein daalte hain, aur wo print ho jata hai. Wahi same code C++ ya Java mein likhne ke liye 5 se 6 lines lagti hain.

**Q. Python high-level kyun hai?**
Kyunki iska code English letters mein likha jata hai (0 aur 1 numbers mein nahi). Saath hi, ye memory management apne aap (automatically) khud kar leta hai.

**Q. Python interpreted kyun hai?**
Ye source file (code) ko line-by-line padhta aur convert karta hai. Jiski wajah se jis line mein problem hoti hai, hamein wahi par error ka pata chal jata hai. Halanki, is line-by-line checking ki wajah se isko run hone mein thoda time lagta hai (thodi slow hoti hai).

**Code jaldi likhna (Fast Development):**
Isme code kaafi chhota hota hai (syntax easy hota hai), isliye hum jaldi code likh kar apna kaam complete kar sakte hain.

**Dynamically Typed:**
Python ek dynamically typed language hai. Yaani isme humein datatype pehle se declare nahi karna padta (jaise `int x = 5`). Ye run time par variable ki value dekh kar khud hi samajh jata hai ki vo kaunsa datatype hai.

